fully completed in March 2010.', 'The United Kingdom made up of England Scotland Wales and Northern Ireland is an island nation in northwestern Europe. England – birthplace of Shakespeare and The Beatles – is home to the capital London a globally influential centre of finance and culture. England is also site of Neolithic Stonehenge Bath’s Roman spa and centuries-old universities at Oxford and Cambridge.', '1', '241930', '33200000', '59.3', '8.9', '50', '133094', '260650', '0.53', '281', '40', '83', '99', '10', '154', 'Northern Europe', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom', 'https://www.britannica.com/place/United-Kingdom', 'https://www.biblesociety.org.uk/', 'https://unitedbiblesocieties.org/locations/british-and-foreign-bible-society/', 'https://www.cia.gov/the-world-factbook/countries/united-kingdom/', 'https://images.bible.cloud/maps/summary/UK-summary.pdf', 'https://hdr.undp.org/data-center/specific-country-data#/countries/USA', 'https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/united_kingdom.htm', 'https://curlie.org/Regional/Europe/United_Kingdom', 'https://operationworld.org/locations/united-kingdom-of-gb-ni', 'https://www.state.gov/countries-areas/united-kingdom/', 'https://joshuaproject.net/countries/GB', 'https://prayercast.com/england.html', 'https://player.vimeo.com/video/37676816', 'http://www.prayercast.com/downloads/direct_download.php?file=England_dload_hi.mov', 'The Holy Bible Abridged; or, The History of the Old and New Testament. Illustrated with Notes and Adorned with Cuts, for the Use of childrens [sic]. The Second Worcester Edition. Worcester, [Mass.]: From the Press of Thomas, Son & Thomas, 1796.<br><br>This 1796 edition of The Holy Bible Abridged is similar in textual content to the 1792 New York edition printed by William Durrell, but includes a different set of illustrations. On display are woodcuts of Christ restoring the widow’s son to life (Luke 7:11–18) and Christ stilling the tempest (Luke 8:41–56).', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
