ling over the peace process but devolution was fully completed in March 2010.', 'The United Kingdom made up of England Scotland Wales and Northern Ireland is an island nation in northwestern Europe. England – birthplace of Shakespeare and The Beatles – is home to the capital London a globally influential centre of finance and culture. England is also site of Neolithic Stonehenge Bath’s Roman spa and centuries-old universities at Oxford and Cambridge.', '1', '241930', '33200000', '59.3', '8.9', '50', '133094', '260650', '0.53', '281', '40', '83', '99', '10', '154', 'Northern Europe', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom', 'https://www.britannica.com/place/United-Kingdom', 'https://www.biblesociety.org.uk/', 'https://unitedbiblesocieties.org/locations/british-and-foreign-bible-society/', 'https://www.cia.gov/the-world-factbook/countries/united-kingdom/', 'https://images.bible.cloud/maps/summary/UK-summary.pdf', 'https://hdr.undp.org/data-center/specific-country-data#/countries/USA', 'https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/united_kingdom.htm', 'https://curlie.org/Regional/Europe/United_Kingdom', 'https://operationworld.org/locations/united-kingdom-of-gb-ni', 'https://www.state.gov/countries-areas/united-kingdom/', 'https://joshuaproject.net/countries/GB', 'https://prayercast.com/england.html', 'https://player.vimeo.com/video/37676816', 'http://www.prayercast.com/downloads/direct_download.php?file=England_dload_hi.mov', 'The New King James Version (NKJV) was commissioned in 1975 by Thomas Nelson Publishers, 130 respected Bible scholars, church leaders, and lay Christians worked for seven years to create a completely new, modern translation of Scripture, yet one that would retain the purity and stylistic beauty of the original King James. With unyielding faithfulness to the original Greek, Hebrew, and Aramaic texts, the translation applies the most recent research in archaeology, linguistics, and textual studies.<br>Copyright © 1982 by Thomas Nelson, Inc. All rights reserved. Used by permission.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
