devolution was fully completed in March 2010.', 'The United Kingdom made up of England Scotland Wales and Northern Ireland is an island nation in northwestern Europe. England – birthplace of Shakespeare and The Beatles – is home to the capital London a globally influential centre of finance and culture. England is also site of Neolithic Stonehenge Bath’s Roman spa and centuries-old universities at Oxford and Cambridge.', '1', '241930', '33200000', '59.3', '8.9', '50', '133094', '260650', '0.53', '281', '40', '83', '99', '10', '154', 'Northern Europe', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom', 'https://www.britannica.com/place/United-Kingdom', 'https://www.biblesociety.org.uk/', 'https://unitedbiblesocieties.org/locations/british-and-foreign-bible-society/', 'https://www.cia.gov/the-world-factbook/countries/united-kingdom/', 'https://images.bible.cloud/maps/summary/UK-summary.pdf', 'https://hdr.undp.org/data-center/specific-country-data#/countries/USA', 'https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/united_kingdom.htm', 'https://curlie.org/Regional/Europe/United_Kingdom', 'https://operationworld.org/locations/united-kingdom-of-gb-ni', 'https://www.state.gov/countries-areas/united-kingdom/', 'https://joshuaproject.net/countries/GB', 'https://prayercast.com/england.html', 'https://player.vimeo.com/video/37676816', 'http://www.prayercast.com/downloads/direct_download.php?file=England_dload_hi.mov', 'Samuel Sharpe, The New Testament, translated from the Text of J.J. Griesbach. London: John Green, 1840. Second edition, 1844; third edition, 1856; fourth edition, 1859; fifth edition, 1862; seventh edition, 1881. A translation of Griesbach 1805, by a Unitarian. Sharpe also published a light revision of the KJV Old Testament in 1865. A one-volume edition of the complete Bible appeared in the year of his death, 1881.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL,