until May 2007 due to wrangling over the peace process but devolution was fully completed in March 2010.', 'The United Kingdom made up of England Scotland Wales and Northern Ireland is an island nation in northwestern Europe. England – birthplace of Shakespeare and The Beatles – is home to the capital London a globally influential centre of finance and culture. England is also site of Neolithic Stonehenge Bath’s Roman spa and centuries-old universities at Oxford and Cambridge.', '1', '241930', '33200000', '59.3', '8.9', '50', '133094', '260650', '0.53', '281', '40', '83', '99', '10', '154', 'Northern Europe', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom', 'https://www.britannica.com/place/United-Kingdom', 'https://www.biblesociety.org.uk/', 'https://unitedbiblesocieties.org/locations/british-and-foreign-bible-society/', 'https://www.cia.gov/the-world-factbook/countries/united-kingdom/', 'https://images.bible.cloud/maps/summary/UK-summary.pdf', 'https://hdr.undp.org/data-center/specific-country-data#/countries/USA', 'https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/united_kingdom.htm', 'https://curlie.org/Regional/Europe/United_Kingdom', 'https://operationworld.org/locations/united-kingdom-of-gb-ni', 'https://www.state.gov/countries-areas/united-kingdom/', 'https://joshuaproject.net/countries/GB', 'https://prayercast.com/england.html', 'https://player.vimeo.com/video/37676816', 'http://www.prayercast.com/downloads/direct_download.php?file=England_dload_hi.mov', 'The goal of The Message is to engage people in the reading process and help them understand what they read. This is not a study Bible, but rather "a reading Bible." The verse numbers, which are not in the original documents, have been left out of the print version to facilitate easy and enjoyable reading. The original books of the Bible were not written in formal language. The Message tries to recapture the Word in the words we use today.<br>Copyright © 1993, 1994, 1995, 1996, 2000, 2001, 2002. Used by permission of NavPress Publishing Group."', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO bibles (_id, abbr, title, iso, script, year, country_id, copyright, copyright_type, bible_links, bible_equivalents, language_iso, language_glotto_id, language_iso1, language_name, language_level, language_country_id, language_latitude, language_longitude, language_population, country_name, country_name_long, country_population, country_official_language, country_official_language_iso, country_iso_a3, country_continent_id, country_iso_num, country_language_count, country_religion_primary, country_introduction, country_overview, country_independent, country_landmass_km, country_population_christian, country_population_christian_percentage, country_population_catholic_percentage, country_population_protestant_percentage, country_population_refugee, country_population_migration, country_population_year_change, country_population_density_km, country_population_average_age, country_population_urban_percentage, country_population_literacy_percentage, country_region_code, country_region_id, country_region_name, country_url_wiki, country_url_britannica, country_url_national_society, country_url_ubs, country_url_factbook, country_url_factbook_pdf, country_url_human_development, country_url_nations_online, country_url_odp, country_url_operation_world, country_url_religious_freedom, country_url_joshua, country_url_prayercast, country_url_prayercast_video, country_url_prayercast_download, description, bible_pod, id, parent_bible_id, uuid, title_vernacular, description_short, description_vernacular, date, alphabet_name, alphabet_script, alphabet_fonts, pod, links, publishers, providers, equivalents, books, gbc, guid, description_reviewed, versification, numeral_system_id, reviewed, isbn13, back_text, cover, questionable, alphabet_unicode_pdf, alphabet_family, alphabet_type, alphabet_white_space, alphabet_open_type_tag, alphabet_complex_positioning, alphabet_requires_font, alphabet_unicode, alphabet_diacritics, alphabet_contextual_forms, alphabet_reordering, alphabet_case, alphabet_split_graphs, alphabet_status, alphabet_baseline, alphabet_ligatures, alphabet_direction, alphabet_direction_notes, alphabet_sample, alphabet_sample_img, alphabet_description, children, language_glotto_family, language_autonym, language_macroarea, language_development, language_use, language_location, language_area, language_progress, language_typology, language_writing, language_description, language_status_id, language_status_notes, language_redirect_to_iso, country_hidden, country_autonym, country_fips, country_wfb, country_wfb_pdf, country_sil_language_count, country_land_mass_km, country_landmass, country) VALUES ('221', 'ENGCOM', 'Commonly Received New Testament', 'eng', 'Latn', '1851', 'GB', 'Public Domain', NULL, '[1 items in bible_links.csv]', NULL, 'eng', 'stan1293', 'en', 'English', 'L', 'GB', '53', '-1', '379000000', 'United Kingdom', 'The United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland', '67081000', 'English', 'eng', 'GBR', 'EU', '826', '101', 'Christianity', 'The United Kingdom has historically played a leading role in developing parliamentary democracy and in advancing literature and science. At its zenith in the 19th century the British Empire stretched over one-fourth of the earth''s surface. The first half of the 20th century saw the UK''s strength seriously depleted in two world wars and the Irish Republic''s withdrawal from the union. The second half witnessed the dismantling of the Empire and the UK rebuilding itself into a modern and prosperous European nation. As one of five permanent members of the UN Security Council and a founding member of NATO and the Commonwealth the UK pursues a global approach to foreign policy. The UK is also an active member of the EU although it chose to remain outside the Economic and Monetary Union. The Scottish Parliament the National Assembly for Wales and the Northern Ireland Assembly were established in 1999. The latter was suspended until May 2007 due to wrangling over the peace process but devolution was fully completed in March 2010.', 'The United Kingdom made up of England Scotland Wales and Northern Ireland is an island nation in northwestern Europe. England – birthplace of Shakespeare and The Beatles – is home to the capital London a globally influential centre of finance and culture. England is also site of Neolithic Stonehenge Bath’s Roman spa and centuries-old universities at Oxford and Cambridge.', '1', '241930', '33200000', '59.3', '8.9', '50', '133094', '260650', '0.53', '281', '40', '83', '99', '10', '154', 'Northern Europe', 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom', 'https://www.britannica.com/place/United-Kingdom', 'https://www.biblesociety.org.uk/', 'https://unitedbiblesocieties.org/locations/british-and-foreign-bible-society/', 'https://www.cia.gov/the-world-factbook/countries/united-kingdom/', 'https://images.bible.cloud/maps/summary/UK-summary.pdf', 'https://hdr.undp.org/data-center/specific-country-data#/countries/USA', 'https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/united_kingdom.htm', 'https://curlie.org/Regional/Europe/United_Kingdom', 'https://operationworld.org/locations/united-kingdom-of-gb-ni', 'https://www.state.gov/countries-areas/united-kingdom/', 'https://joshuaproject.net/countries/GB', 'https://prayercast.com/england.html', 'https://player.vimeo.com/video/37676816', 'http://www.prayercast.com/downloads/direct_download.php?file=England_dload_hi.mov', 'The Commonly Received Version of the New Testament of Our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ, with Several Hundred Emendations, edited by Spencer H. Cone and William H. Wyckoff. New York: Lewis Colby, 1850.<br><br>Spencer Houghton Cone was born in Princeton, New Jersey, April 13, 1785. He entered Princeton University at the age of twelve, but two years later, because of his father’s illness, left his studies. At sixteen he was master in a school at Burlington. <br><br>He was converted to the Baptist Church in 1814. In 1815-1816 he became Chaplain of the United States House of Representatives. About 1823, he moved to the Oliver street church, New York, where he remained for eighteen years. He then became pastor of the 1st Baptist church there. In 1832, he became president of the Baptist triennial convention, and was re-elected until 1841. From 1837 till 1850 he was president of the American and foreign Bible society. On the formation of the American Bible union, he was made its president, and so continued until his death on August 28, 1855.<br><br>At the zenith of his career he was probably the most popular and influential Baptist minister in the United States.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
